events.name: DevFest'17
events.description:
Google Developer Group Udaipur organises DevFest'17 in association with Sanskrut Corporation as Board Of Advisors and sponsored by GKMIT  . Our Online Media Partners include UdaipurBlog .  GDG DevFests are large, community-run developer events happening around the globe focused on community building and learning about Google’s technologies. It is like a global series of events which take place between Aug to Nov in various different countries across the globe .

                Date: 4th Nov' 2017 

                Time:10:00 am to 3:00 pm

                Venue: Placement Cell, CTAE Udaipur . 

 The speakers for the event are : 

• Harsha Bandaru  is currently a Full Stack Developer at Ellipsoid ECM Tech . He works on Android (XML, Kotlin and Java) . He is currently CTO at WieLabs, Hyderabad .  In the past , he has worked with Google Hyderabad as Senior Application Analyst . He is also an active contributor at Google Developer Group Hyderabad . 

Topic for talk : Kotlin 

• Avikalp Kumar Gupta  - has pursued his  Bachelor's Degree from Computer Science Department of IIT Kanpur . In IIT Kanpur, he has studied courses about concepts of Machine Learning (Basic Introduction, Probabilistic Machine Learning , Online Learning etc. ) as well as its application in problems like NLP, Computer Vision, Robotics etc. He has also worked with Microsoft Research (India) for a year . He is currently working with a social start up where he is trying to leverage technology to solve a social problem .

Topic for talk:

Machine Learning 

• Jeetesh Sisodia - Mr. Jeetesh is the founder of GKMIT - a family of engineers, designers and innovators with expertise in making a business idea turn into a technical reality . He is a Full Stack Developer specialising in Ruby On Rails (RoR) with hands on experience of 7+ years . He is currently CTO on Reshotel, Mumbai (Cloud based channel manager for 27 OTAs) and VP Engineering in Bitssa, London (Cyrpto Currency Exchange for emerging world) . He loves prototyping different product ideas with his team and keeping himself updated on the start up ecosystem .

Topic for talk: Ruby On Rails 


• Pradeep Chauhan - Mr. Pradeep is an iOS developer specialized in Swift with hands on experience of more than 2.5 years. He is currently working in GKMIT, as an iOS developer and handling complex applications for multiple projects. He is Senior Lead on Reshotel (Cloud based channel manager for 27 OTAs).He is also an admin on 5 social iOS developer communities in India and helps different developers on iPhone application development.He is also an active blogger on Medium and has created few open source libraries in Swift language.He enjoys keeping himself updated on backend frameworks and loves brainstorming with backend team for creation of RESTful API’s.

Topic for talk: Swift for beginners 

Registration is open, use link https://goo.gl/EUPUCA to register for the event  . Doing RSVP in this event is not the registration! We will filter out registered entries and will send out final confirmation mails with confirmation id enclosed .

events.name: Google I/O Extended 2018
events.description:
Google Developer Group Udaipur organises I/O Extended in association with Sanskrut Corporation as Board Of Advisors.

Google I/O (simply I/O) is an annual developer conference held by Google in San Francisco, California. I/O showcases technical in-depth sessions focused on building web, mobile, and enterprise applications with Google and open sources such as Android, Chrome and Chrome OS, APIs, Google Web Toolkit, App Engine, and more. I/O Extended events include a variety of options for developers—from live streaming sessions to local demos, hackathons, codelabs, and more. The motive is to deliver the same kind of Google I/O Experience in our own hometown Udaipur.

Date: 30th June' 2018

Time:10:00 am to 3:00 pm

Venue: Ashoka Palace, 2, 100 Feet Rd, Rupsagar, Udaipur.

Agenda For The Meetup : -

1) Keynote and Announcements At Google I/O 2018

2) Session On How to develop Projects Remotely And Also Contribute To Open Source by Puneet Sahalot .

3) Lunch & Networking Break

4) Talk On Flutter by Dhrumil Shah

5) Code-lab On Flutter by Dhrumil Shah
Note: Please bring your laptops and datapack with you for the codelab session on Flutter .

The speakers for the event are :

• Dhrumil Shah the co-organiser of GDG Ahmedabad and a Mobile Developer at Shipments & founder of @Flutter_Flakes
Who has started working with Android when Android 2.1 was announced & now exploring cross-platform technologies like React Native and Flutter.
He has done Masters in Computer Engineering in Wireless and Mobile Computing. Being an expert, he has an excellent command over developing applications that have made him a good trainer as well as an avid speaker in his domain. He often organises workshops, seminars and talks to help developers & students who look forward to growing their careers in the field of Mobile Computing.

Topic for the talk: Flutter

• Puneet Sahalot is the Founder Of IdeaBox Creations. He has worked as an independent consultant and developer for renowned web agencies. Puneet has made amazing contributions to the development community and is always ever ready to foster and build communities. He is also leading WordPress community meetups in Udaipur.

Topic for the talk: How to be a professional freelancer and also contribute to open source.

events.name: DevFest 2019
events.description:
Google Developer Group Udaipur organizes DevFest 2019 in association with Sanskrut Corporation as Board Of Advisors, Tie Udaipur as Title Sponsor.

GDG DevFests are large, community-run developer events happening around the globe focused on community building and learning about Google’s technologies. It is like a global series of events that take place between Aug to Nov in various different countries across the globe.

Date:- 28th September 2019

Time :- 10:00 AM - 4:00 PM

Venue:- Laziz Affairs, Roof Top, Manglam Fun Square Mall, 8th Floor, 12, Durga Nursery Road, Shakti Nagar, Udaipur, Rajasthan[masked]

The agenda of the event is as follows:-

1) High Tea and Registration Process

2) Talk On "Flutter Everywhere" by Sanni Prasad.

Sanni is an organiser for Flutter Ahemdabad Community. He loves organising informative sessions and study Jam.

3) Talk on "Building AI: What It Really Takes?" by Rohit Ghosh.

Rohit is a Google Developer Expert of Machine Learning, TEDx Speaker and Founding Member of Qure.ai. Rohit’s most recent co-authored research was published in The Lancet - world’s oldest and most prestigious general medical journal. In fact, this was The Lancet's first ever publication on AI-in-imaging. Rohit is a graduate from IIT Bombay. He has worked as data science consultant to multiple global EdTech startups in developing their data science course curriculum. He’s also a Faculty for Machine Learning at multiple data science startups, and of late been a Visiting Faculty at MPSTME, NMIMS University. Rohit had also been invited in the past to conduct multiple data science workshops in Manchester & London for business executives. He has also been advising another IIT Bombay based group for developing reinforcement learning AI for stock market trading. In his work as AI Scientist, he has closely worked with Yale School of Medicine on applications of AI in predicting survival for cardiac failure patients which was later published in Journal of American Heart Association. He has also presented his research at the European Society of Radiology Conference, 2018 at Vienna, Austria. His other co-authored research was presented at annual conferences (2017, 2018) by Radiological Society of North America at Chicago, USA. His research work was also accepted for presentation at annual conference organized by African Society of Radiology at Cairo, Egypt.

4) Quiz Contest hosted by Jayant Ojha and Praveen Soni.

5) Lunch and Networking Break

6) Talk on "Choosing The Right GCP Product: Compute Edition" by Dharmesh Vaya.

Dharmesh is a Google Developer Expert, Google Cloud and Solutions Architect known for his ability of developing enterprise applications on Cloud Platforms and fostering a spirit of innovation among teams. Currently heading one of the Engineering divisions responsible for Software Environments/Cloud Architecture with a focus on Automation technologies. He is actively managing Google Cloud Developers Community, Mumbai and speaks at various conferences. He actively guides and mentors Students, Young Professionals as well as local businesses on Cloud Technologies on the Google Cloud Platform. If found offline, he might be wandering into some Himalayan trekking expeditions.

7) Workshop on #IamRemarkable by Hiral Thaker.

Hiral Thaker is working as a content writer, Redhat Certified System Administrator and WTM Facilitator.

8) Fireside Chat with TiE Udaipur.

This section is hosted by Vikas Jain. Vikas is Executive Director, TiE Udaipur.

events.name: #IamRemarkable Workshop
events.description:
We are excited to share that we're organizing #IamRemarkable workshop!:) The event is organized in association with Sanskrut Corporation as Board of Advisors.

#IamRemarkable is a Google initiative empowering women and underrepresented groups to speak openly about their accomplishments in the workplace and beyond, thereby breaking modesty norms and glass ceilings.

Workshop's goals: - Improve the self-promotion motivation and skills; - Challenge the social perception around self-promotion.

What awaits you? In this interactive session, you will participate in group discussions and exercises to develop the conﬁdence and skills to promote yourself effectively. The workshop will highlight to participants the importance of self-promotion in their careers and provide them with the tools to practice this skill.

Places are limited to 20 per session, so please RSVP by registering for this event on meetup.

The workshop is facilitated by Punita Ojha.
